Rex Macey at @RinFinance: Optimization (LP) for wealth management. Tax efficiency, better constraints, sell variables for each tax lot. Uses scenarios instead of covariance matrix; wants to avoid big losses but also avoid missing good times. #rstats #rfinance

G() comes from differentiable neural net; yields nonlinear stochastic discount factor. Deep PLS performs very nicely out of sample for small/sensible number of factors for both stocks and portfolios. #rstats #rfinance

David Ardia at @RinFinance: misspecification of factor models inflates estimated hedge fund alpha. (CAPM, FF3, Carhart, Fung-Hsieh all insufficient.) Better specified model (variance, illiquidity, bet against beta, carry, ts momentum) shows much lower alpha. #rstats #rfinance
R package: hofa (higher order factor analysis) https://t.co/mDXKQ0Vpf9 and paper https://t.co/1f6VkyD7Cq #rstats #rfinance
Emile Lemahieu at @RinFinance: Portfolio drawdown optimization using generative ML. Does better than min vol, min drawdown (historic). #rstats #rfinance

Michael Kane @kaneplusplus at @RinFinance on pharmacofinance: finance of drug development. Inefficiencies in drug development can be large: phase 2 (enrollers may gum up start if not pleased w/deal), market in phase 3. #rstats #rfinance

Steven Pav @shabbychef at @RinFinance: Performance Estimation w/the Sharpe Ratio. Is SR signaal-noise ratio? t-stat-ish? a bit of both? Features SharpeR, MarkowitzR packages. Check out his book on the Sharpe Ratio! #rstats #rfinance

Kris Boudt @OptimizeRisk kicks off the return of R/Finance @RinFinance with how to do better PCA to find factors when idiosyncratic volatility is high: use coskewness to tease out factors. #rstats #rfinance

Matthew Dixon @mfrdixon keynotes @RinFinance on deep partial least squares to improve factor modeling. Many factors nonlinear in effect, some latent. Find Y, X projections p, then regress Y-score on X-score by maximizing (Xp)'Yp w/G() Taylor series to linearize. #rstats #rfinance

Majeed Simaan @simaan84 at @RinFinance: Pricing Model Complexity and Volatility-Managed Portfolios. Accumulated local effects get interpretability of ML, measure+decompose complexity a la Molnar et al (2019). Sees tradeoffs of complexity. #rstats #rfinance
Seth Therrien ⚡️ at @RinFinance: Code Architecture for a Mid-Term Trading Strategy. RStudio+data.table+Ranger, data quality handling, feature engineer, model, backtest, execute. #rstats #rfinance

Ryan Brown at @RinFinance: Portfolio Performance Attribution w/ML. Perf attribution: returns (FF) vs holding->factors (Barra) vs holdings->allocation+selection (Brinson). Classification+regression trees using style factors. #rstats #rfinance

Jerzy Pawlowski at @RinFinance: Fast Backtest Simulation of Trading Strategies. Markowitz? Unstable, overfit. Markowitz w/parameter shrinkage? Slow. Regularized inverse/dim reduction? Better out-of-sample. Add return shrinkage? Even better! #rstats #rfinance

Veronika Ročková keynotes at @RinFinance: Bayesian Sparsity. Spike+slab LASSO: shrink noise->0 but not signal. Sparse priors + rotations to get sparse PCA. Dynamic S+S LASSO w/vertical, horizontal sparsity, smoothness! SSLASSO package. #rstats #rfinance

Ilya Kipnis @QuantStratTradR at @RinFinance: Significantly reducing turnover in tactical asset allocation with this one weird trick.  Punish the momentum of assets small/not in portfolio. #rstats #rfinance

#RStats

@ozjimbob An idle eventloop in raw 'tcl' isn't too difficult.

What *is* difficult is stopping it!

library(tcltk)
dit <- function(...) {
  cat(".")
  tcltk::tcl('after', 100, dit)
}

tcltk::tcl('after', 100, dit)
Sys.sleep(5)

# Cancel the loop
tcltk::tcl('after', 'cancel', dit)
